{{en-noun|-}}

# <!--{{historical}} commented out historical tag since it's to be used for things which no longer exist. it seems odd to suggest that hell or damnation no longer exist. perhaps archaic or obsolete were intended?--> The act or process of damnation or [[reprobation]]; [[Hell]].
#: ''What in '''tarnation''' is going on.''

====Usage notes====
This New Englandism has fallen out of usage, but is remembered for its colorfulness. It was often used as a minced interjection, where ‘hell’ or ‘damn’ might have been said instead.